Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: Low risk

Quote:"IMMerge was a phase III, international, multicentre, randomized, open-label, efficacy–assessor-blinded, active-comparator study of up to 88 weeks’ total duration...The study included a 30-day screening period, and eligible patients were randomized in a 1 : 1 ratio via a centralized Interactive Response Technology system to open-label treatment with risankizumab or secuk- inumab for up to 64 weeks "
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int:
Quote:"IMMerge was a phase III, international, multicentre, randomized, open-label, efficacy–assessor-blinded, active-comparator study of up to 88 weeks’ total duration"

Quote:"Efficacy endpoints were determined using the intent-to-treat population, defined as all patients randomized at baseline."
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support:
9.1% of the participants in the risankizumab group and 19% of the participants in the secukinumab group discontinued by week 52. 

The reasons for discontinuation were imbalanced between the two groups. 

Missingness could depend on the true value of the outcome
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo:
The measurement was appropriate. 

Although the study was not blinded, PASI 90 is considered an objective outcome and ascertainement was probably the same in both groups.
Overall.bias.support: At least one domain at high risk of bias
